    "name": "committed_2016_sigmoid",
    "description": "Maps the committed_split threshold in the 2016-block retarget regime with the sigmoid price oracle enabled. Companion to committed_2016_high_econ (same econ=0.78, baseline).\nRESEARCH QUESTION: Sigmoid halved cascade time (8426s \u2192 4239s) and halved v26 block accumulation (1543 \u2192 799) at committed_split=0.35. Does sigmoid LOWER the committed_split threshold? If sigmoid fires the cascade earlier, v27 might win even with a lower committed_split where baseline fails.\nMECHANISM: Sigmoid amplifies the price signal: larger price gaps \u2192 faster neutral pool drift \u2192 v27 accumulates 2016 blocks faster. At low committed_split values where baseline v27 stalls (not enough hashrate to hit 2016 blocks before v26 retargets), sigmoid's faster neutral pool convergence might tip the balance.\nPRIOR CONTEXT: - At committed_split=0.35 with sigmoid: cascade_t=4239s vs 8426s baseline (2x faster) - v26 block count drops from 1543 to 799 with sigmoid (fewer v26 blocks before cascade) - At econ=0.82 (2 nodes): cascade so fast (607s) that sigmoid makes no difference - Peak price gap: 21.6% sigmoid vs 16.1% baseline at 1-node econ level\nEXPECTED OUTCOMES: - committed_split=0.50: v27 wins with both oracles \u2014 sigmoid fires faster - committed_split=0.30: baseline may stall, sigmoid may still win (threshold test) - committed_split=0.20: probably v26_dominant even with sigmoid\nCOMMITTED_SPLIT INTERPRETATION:\n  committed_split=0.20: v27=14%, v26=56%, neutral=30%\n  committed_split=0.30: v27=21%, v26=49%, neutral=30%\n  committed_split=0.40: v27=28%, v26=42%, neutral=30%\n  committed_split=0.50: v27=35%, v26=35%, neutral=30%  (symmetric)\n\nRun command:\n  python tools/sweep/3_run_sweep.py \\\n    --input tools/sweep/committed_2016_sigmoid/build_manifest.json \\\n    --namespace sweep-com2016-sig \\\n    --results-dir committed_2016_sigmoid/results \\\n    --duration 13000 --retarget-interval 2016 --interval 2 \\\n    --use-sigmoid\n\nNamespace to create first:\n  kubectl create namespace sweep-com2016-sig\n\nWall-clock: 4 scenarios \u00d7 13,000s = 52,000s \u2248 14.4h\n",
